node.text:
I was a volunteer firefighter outside of Tucson, Az. My Chief, Danny Martin, showed me then the bond that comes from the communal intensity experienced day in and day out fighting fires as well as in the firehouses. The only other time I experienced anything close to that was doing “Only the Brave” when every breath we inhaled and exhaled was in conscious honor of those who really put themselves out there for their own and their surrounding communities. 
My love and condolences go out to the families and friends left behind and especially to @ericmarshfoundationfire (Amanda) and @donut_928 (Brendan). I love you both very much.  My forever respect to those who truly walk the line. #granitemountainhotshots #yarnell19

node.text:
have come and gone and new judgements are percolating on their stilted way — and once the word has survived all songs and the orator has licked its lip and rounded out another sound readied to spring, we will still want to be listening for that mirror that is us seen through another shard of glass that is what perspective may be. 
Yes, once all the judgement of what businesses may lift and crumble exhales, there will always be a little simple us to create from the thin air of our imaginations and from the foibles of our choices inhaled. 
This, spoken Tony. This Tony spoken. When all the stars reignite and all the clouds, for a moment, take a bow. 
Love you, buddy. You are so beautifully you/all of us.

——

node.text: There is nothing like knowing in the midst of a major alien crisis that someone is running toward it hoping to be of service to someone in direct peril. It’s the mother lifting the car off the child. It’s the person who pulls someone out of a totally inflamed car. It is those firefighters who, step after step, lunged toward those frighted into paralyses, even after one tower had already come down. Firefighters in my life have, by far, revealed themselves to have the greatest character, possess the most humility and compassion, and just be downright fun/good people. My heart goes out to the families and friends of those who died on that unnecessary and totally unfortunate day 20 years ago. New York came together and I’ll always be moved by the respect paid to those heroic (and hero-laymen) deaths. The most respectful thing we can do in reaction is to be active in giving each day the respect it deserves and treat those around you like it’s your last. Fuck Osama Bin Laden and fuck anyone in our government who doesn’t look out for the citizens they’re there to represent.#firefighterslife

node.text:
I am living the painter’s life.  I brushstroke through each day and along with God, and some friends, people I meet, some to come, some to go, I pirouette on this canvas that those before us played, built and ruined. And now is our turn, these choices to swim through, with giggling children on our shoulders, sometimes crying — the streets tungsten lit, yellowy and stained with a wine that I stopped drinking years ago. 
Grateful to even move, feel, taste this morning. I got on my knees to touch thanks, lean over to taste my wife’s neglected lips, then went upstairs to inhale the scent of the tops of my babies heads. Thanks for it all, even, yes, being able to paint this circus canvas with what is me in the little ways that I am able and that I’m not totally fucking useless through it all. ❤️🙏 Photo by @kathrynbrolin

node.text: Italy. I love you. You have always been kind to me, my family, my friends. I believe you when you say you like the film, as I’ve always found you all straight shooters. Our cast is proud of our movie because between all of us (under the warmly watchful eye and support of Denis Villeneuve) we went big (but never impersonal). A film isn’t independent because of some esoteric song that’s hard to find, or it has no budget. It’s indy at heart because it uses art to identify people. “Dune” does that. “Star Wars” did that. It’s bigger than us, yet it is us. So thank you, Italy, and everyone who has embraced our film so far. We appreciate it more than you know. Grazie di tutto. 🇮🇹 @dolcegabbana @samanthamcmillen_stylist (@greigfraser_dp We missed you, buddy ❤️)

node.text:
Something happens deeply in the soul with music. It might be as simple as birds chirping in a morning with sun rays peaking through heavy cloud cover or it might feel as if a sound, an orchestra of a repression, has come back to rage against the paranoia of a time. Not a molecule of talent lost, these sounds come forth as a storm that raises a fire igniting us all — the wail of a strangled note, held.
Tonight threw me into a reverie of being a kid with my mother in some ratty old blues bar in New Orleans surround by nothing but a pulsing, almost spastic possession of the music. Transported — Mama’s home again. 
Chris and Morgane crawl in the dirt, pull you through fields of feelings and the ghosts follow you home. Like listening to Pavarotti hit his high C during “Nessun Dorma”, something ignited in me and the world is suddenly full of hope. And that hope lives in the people, a remembrance of what it is to love something with total abandon. The romance of it. The insanity in it. The poetry in fully being a human fallible being. 
Thank you Chris and Morgane (and band mates) for lighting up Georgia tonight and for making us (the family) feel right at home with your down home embraces. @chrisstapleton @morganestapleton @kathrynbrolin @kaylinbuckley @healthbyheighlen #thetattooedwonder #seanycakes
